efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N * M) where N = s.length(), M = words[0].length()
space complexity: O(W) where W = number of distinct words
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sliding-window over each offset mod wordLen to avoid redundant scans; uses two hash maps to compare frequencies in O(1) per word. Early exits and minimal string creation keep CPU and memory traffic low.

